ZQ","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":39690,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/03\/24\/do-not-argue-rasul\/","url_meta":{"origin":23054,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Sunnah: Do not dispute with the Prophet","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 24, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cLeave me with what I have left for you. When I narrate a saying to you, take it from me. Verily, those before you were only ruined because they excessively interrogated and disputed their prophets.\u201d Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11071,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/06\/arguments-people-astray-argue\/","url_meta":{"origin":23054,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Arguments: People led astray by bickering","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 6, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Umamah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNo people are led astray after being guided but that they indulged in arguments.\u201d Then, the Prophet recited the verse, \u201cThey strike an example for you only to argue. Rather, they are a quarrelsome people.\u201d (43:58)\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24522,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/03\/16\/house-paradise-husn-khuluq\/","url_meta":{"origin":23054,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Adab: House in paradise for those with good character","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 16, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever abandons lies in support of falsehood, a house will be built for him in the surroundings of Paradise. Whoever abandons arguments even though he is right, a house will be built for him in\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3766,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/23\/breaks-fast-same-reward\/","url_meta":{"origin":23054,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: Help break fast, earn same reward","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 23, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Zayd ibn Khalid reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever helps break the fast of a fasting person, he will have the same reward as him without decreasing anything from the reward of the fasting person.\" Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 807 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6083,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/08\/love-your-akh-let-him-know\/","url_meta":{"origin":23054,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Brothers: If you love your brother, let him know","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 8, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Miqdam ibn Ma\u2019dikarib reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen one of you loves his brother, let him know.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2392 Grade:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to Al-Tirmidhi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u0650\u0642\u0652\u062f\u064e\u0627\u0645\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0639\u0652\u062f\u0650\u064a\u0643\u064e\u0631\u0650\u0628\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0630\u064e\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u062d\u064e\u0628\u064e\u0651 \u0623\u064e\u062d\u064e\u062f\u064f\u0643\u064f\u0645\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u062e\u064e\u0627\u0647\u064f \u0641\u064e\u0644\u0652\u064a\u064f\u0639\u0652\u0644\u0650\u0645\u0652\u0647\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":16115,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/09\/16\/do-not-gloat-over-your-brother\/","url_meta":{"origin":23054,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Malice: Do not gloat over your brother\u2019s hardship","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 16, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Wathilah ibn Al-Asqa' reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cDo not rejoice over the misfortune of your brother, lest Allah have mercy upon him and afflict you with trials.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2506 Grade: Hasan (fair) accordi